 is closed. Text A has tall I in line three. The primary difference between Text A and Text B is in the technique, with the letters in A having a flat cut, whereas B is engraved with a more elegant 'v-cut' and more elegant interpuncts. It is likely that the two were carved by different stone-masons.",[296,300,304,308,312,316,320,323,326,329],{"type":34,"l":297,"from":298,"to":298,"h":299,"unit":37},"Line A 1","lineA1","37-39",{"type":34,"l":301,"from":302,"to":302,"h":303,"unit":37},"Line A 2","lineA2","32-35",{"type":34,"l":305,"from":306,"to":306,"h":307,"unit":37},"Line A 3","lineA3","27-33",{"type":34,"l":309,"from":310,"to":310,"h":311,"unit":37},"Line B 1","lineB1","35",{"type":34,"l":313,"from":314,"to":314,"h":315,"unit":37},"Line B 2","lineB2","30",{"type":34,"l":317,"from":318,"to":318,"h":319,"unit":37},"Line B 3","lineB3","27-29",{"type":39,"l":321,"from":298,"to":302,"h":322,"unit":37},"Interlineation line A1 to A2","12",{"type":39,"l":324,"from":302,"to":306,"h":325,"unit":37},"Interlineation line A2 to A3","11-13",{"type":39,"l":327,"from":310,"to":314,"h":328,"unit":37},"Interlineation line B1-B2","10",{"type":39,"l":330,"from":314,"to":318,"h":328,"unit":37},"Interlineation line B2-B3",{"_":332,"notBefore":333,"notAfter":334},"Perhaps between 16 BCE and 4 CE",-16,4,[336,337],{"_":48,"type":49,"ref":50},{"_":52,"type":53,"ref":54},[339],[57,58],{"_":62,"role":63,"ref":64},{"_":342,"type":343},"22522","inventory",{"_":345,"mainLang":346,"languages":347},"Latin","la",[345],{"n":70,"url":349,"height":72,"width":73,"desc":350,"surfaceType":75},"ISic003324A_tiled.tif","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo, Agrigento",[],[353,354,355,356,357,90,358],"De Miro, 1984-1985, L'attivita della soprintendenza archeologica di Agrigento (Anni 1980-84)","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano","De Miro, 2000, Agrigento nella prima età imperiale","Pugliese Carratelli and Fiorentini, 1992, Agrigento, Museo Archeologico",